'''Kirovs Lipmans''' (born 5 November 1940, [[Liepāja]]) is a Latvian Jewish businessman and former <ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportacentrs.com/hokejs/latvijas_izlases/07102016-lipmanu_nomet_no_trona_par_latvijas_hokej/?player=40 |title= Lipmanu nomet no troņa, par Latvijas hokeja vadītāju kļūst Kalvītis |publisher=sportacentrs.com |language=Latvian |date=2016-10-07 |accessdate=2016-10-08}}</ref> president of the national [[Latvian Ice Hockey Federation]] since 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sergejazoltokafonds.lv/lat/varoni/?player=40 |title=Lipmans Kirovs |publisher=Sergeja Žoltoka Fonds |language=Latvian |accessdate=2010-11-01}}</ref> Since 2003, Lipmans is also [[Chair (official)|chairman]] of the [[Riga Stock Exchange|Riga OMX exchange]] listed pharmaceutical company [[Grindeks]], where he also is the largest shareholder.<ref name="AR2009p4">{{cite web |url=http://www.nasdaqomxbaltic.com/upload/reports/grd/2009_ar_en_eur_con_ias.pdf |title=Joint Stock Company “Grindeks” Annual Report 2009 |publisher=nasdacomxbaltic.com |page=4 |date=2010-04-27 |accessdate=2010-11-01}}</ref>
On 12 April 2001, Lipmans was awarded the [[Order of the Three Stars]] (4th class), whilst he was chairman of the Riga OMX exchange listed company [[Liepājas Metalurgs]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.president.lv/images/modules/items/PDF/item_1543_ordenis.pdf |title=Latvijas Triju Zvaigžņu Ordenis 1994–2004 |publisher=president.lv |page=22 |language=Latvian |accessdate=2010-11-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716083334/http://www.president.lv/images/modules/items/PDF/item_1543_ordenis.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-16 |df= }}</ref>
