{{Infobox person | name = Marcel Deléon | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 9 May 1894 | birth_place = [[Villard-de-Lans]], [[Isère]], France | death_date = {{d-da|4 September 1967|9 May 1894}} | death_place = Paris, France | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | residence = | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | alma mater = | employer = | occupation = Businessman, historian | title = | salary = | networth = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = }} '''Marcel Deléon''' (1894-1967) was a French businessman and historian.<ref name="bnfmarcel">{{cite web|title=Marcel Deléon (1894-1967)|url=http://data.bnf.fr/12471168/marcel_deleon/|website=[[Bibliothèque nationale de France]]|accessdate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> He won the Prix Marcelin Guérin from the [[Académie française]] for ''Le nid de l’aigle. Voyage à l'île d'Elbe'' in 1935.<ref name="academiemarcel">{{cite web|title=Marcel DELÉON|url=http://www.academie-francaise.fr/marcel-deleon|website=[[Académie française]]|accessdate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>
